comment_text: Rosogolla is not supposed to be spongy. It was made so for the commercial market so that it can withstand the shocks while in the can. My entire life i had rosogolla which were soft , slightly warm and melts in the mouth with a simple bite. That jiggly softness with mild taste of chena just makes me nostalgic. I remember their were rosogolla karigars who used to come to my nannyтАЩs and make those buckets and buckets of rosogollas for every celebration or function. They used to mock the sponginess of canned kolkata rosogolla saying what non sense are those.
author: Saptarshi Ghosh
